  "prompt": "Should organic peanut butter be refrigerated?",
  "response": "Organic peanut butter does not necessarily need to be refrigerated, but doing so can help maintain its freshness and prevent the natural oils from separating. If you prefer a thicker consistency, refrigeration is a good option. However, if you like it softer and easier to spread, you may choose to store it at room temperature. Just ensure the lid is tightly closed to keep it from becoming rancid. If the oils do separate, stirring the peanut butter can help recombine them. Always check the label for any specific storage instructions from the manufacturer.",
